   <section>
     <h1><i><font color = "440088"><center>HOW TO SOLVE A WORD PROBLEM:  By Ben McGahee</center></font></i></h1>
   </section>
   <p class="centeredImage"><img src="Ben.jpg" height="200" width="200"></p>
    <header>
    <p> 
      <h3><u><font color = "ff6600">STEP 1</font></u></h3><h4>Read the problem carefully.</h4>
    </p>
    <p>
       <h3><u><font color = "ff6600">STEP 2</font></u></h3><h4>Identify the known value(s) and unknown value(s) in the problem.</h4>
    </p>
    <p>
       <h3><u><font color = "ff6600">STEP 3</font></u></h3><h4>Declare variables for the unknown value(s) in the problem and set up equation(s).</h4>
    </p>
    <p>
       <h3><u><font color = "ff6600">STEP 4</font></u></h3><h4>Solve the equation(s) for the unknown value(s).</h4>
    </p>
    <p>
       <h3><u><font color = "ff6600">STEP 5</font></u></h3><h4>Check your answer(s) to see if everything makes sense.</h4>
    </p>
